    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">The Three Strands of Triple Helix Creative</h2>
    <p>To make this feel cohesive, you can present these three areas as an integrated lifecycle of design:</p>

    <pre class="overflow-x-auto bg-slate-100 p-4 rounded-lg text-sm leading-6">
         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
         │                  TRIPLE HELIX CREATIVE                  │
         └───────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                                     │
         ┌───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────┐
         ▼                           ▼                             ▼
  [ EARTH SYSTEMS ]           [ PEOPLE SYSTEMS ]            [ BODY SYSTEMS ]
  • Permaculture              • Digital UI/UX               • Ergonomics
  • Soil & Water              • Web Architectures           • Spatial Flow
  • Ecological Design         • Comm. Platforms             • Internal Living
    </pre>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">🧬 Strand 1: Earth Systems (Ecological & Permacultural)</h3>
    <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li><strong>The Pitch:</strong> Designing with, not against, the natural world.</li>
      <li><strong>The Focus:</strong> Water catchment, soil building, edible landscapes, and regenerative food forests.</li>
      <li><strong>The Connection:</strong> This is your outer zone—designing the physical, living environment that sustains us.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">🧬 Strand 2: People Systems (Digital & Social)</h3>
    <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li><strong>The Pitch:</strong> Structuring how we connect, communicate, and share information.</li>
      <li><strong>The Focus:</strong> High-performance web architectures, custom digital platforms, intuitive user interfaces, and communication tools.</li>
      <li><strong>The Connection:</strong> This is your virtual zone—designing the modern systems that allow groups, communities, or businesses to collaborate and thrive seamlessly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">🧬 Strand 3: Body & Member Systems (Spatial & Living)</h3>
    <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li><strong>The Pitch:</strong> Optimizing the immediate spaces where the human body lives, moves, and works.</li>
      <li><strong>The Focus:</strong> Internal spatial layouts, functional living arrangements, workspace ergonomics, and the physical flow of a home or studio.</li>
      <li><strong>The Connection:</strong> This is your inner zone—designing the immediate physical envelope that supports daily human life, comfort, and productivity.</li>
    </ul>
